---
import MarketingLayout from '../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="About | Insight Hunter"
  description="Insight Hunter gives small businesses CFO-level clarity, systems, and execution without enterprise overhead."
>
  <section class="container section split">
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1>Built for operators who need answers, not noise.</h1>
      <p>Insight Hunter combines bookkeeping, analytics, planning, and execution tools so small businesses can run with more control and less guesswork.</p>
      <p>The goal is simple: make enterprise-grade visibility accessible to founders, accountants, bookkeepers, and growing teams.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="panel">
      <h2>What we optimize for</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Clarity over dashboards for dashboard’s sake.</li>
        <li>Actionable reporting over passive metrics.</li>
        <li>Low-friction adoption for real small-business teams.</li>
        <li>Modular tools instead of bloated all-in-one software.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container section values">
    <article class="panel"><h2>Finance-first</h2><p>P&amp;L, cash flow, forecasting, compliance, and reporting are core, not add-ons.</p></article>
    <article class="panel"><h2>Operational</h2><p>Every product is meant to push decisions, tasks, and execution forward.</p></article>
    <article class="panel"><h2>Expandable</h2><p>Teams can start with one app and grow into a complete operating stack.</p></article>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>

<style>
  .container { max-width: 1180px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.25rem; }
  .section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .split { display: grid; gap: 1.25rem; grid-template-columns: 1.3fr .9fr; }
  .values { display: grid; gap: 1rem; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px,1fr)); }
  .panel { border: 1px solid rgba(84,72,56,.14); border-radius: 18px; padding: 1.25rem; }
  .eyebrow { text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .12em; font-size: .8rem; opacity: .7; }
  @media (max-width: 840px) { .split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
